# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.eggs/
build/
dist/
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
# coverage.py artifacts — binary, bake in absolute dev-machine paths (a PUBLISH_LEAK
# floor hit), and are a per-run test byproduct, never a shippable file.
.coverage
.coverage.*
htmlcov/
coverage.xml
.venv/
venv/

# Local secrets — operator-supplied tokens (Slack bot token, etc.). NEVER
# tracked: a committed token is the exact supply-chain hazard SECURITY.md warns
# about. Keep the shape documented in a tracked .env.example, the values local.
.env
.env.local

# The pre-publish leak scanner — private-side tooling that NEVER ships (it
# documents the very patterns it forbids, and EXCLUDEs itself from its own
# scan, so committing it would both leak and pass CI). A maintainer keeps a
# local copy here so the gate runs on this clone too (CI's leak-scan job runs
# it when present, skips when absent); ignored so no `git add` can stage it.
scripts/leak_scan.py

# DOS state / scratch (re-derivable; never tracked in the OS repo itself —
# the OS is stateless about which workspace it serves)
_scratch/
*.err
.dos-workspace/
.dos/

# Private GOCACHE used to run the Go suite off the shared cache lock (see the
# go-test cache-lock note). It bakes absolute build paths into its object files,
# so it MUST stay untracked — otherwise the pre-publish leak scan flags it.
.gocache*/

# Throwaway WSL helper scripts (they cd into the dev machine's WSL mount of this
# checkout). Untracked scratch; ignored so they can never be swept into the public
# seed copy.
_wsl_*.sh

# The EnterpriseOps-Gym clone (docs/143/144 live A/B) — a separate upstream repo
# (ServiceNow/EnterpriseOps-Gym, multi-GB with seed DBs), NEVER vendored into DOS.
# CRITICALLY this also keeps conf/llm/*.json (which carries the Gemini API key) out
# of the tree. The DOS-side harness (dos_react.py / run_ab.py / intervention_*.py /
# live_ab.py) IS tracked; the clone and live-run outputs are not.
benchmark/enterpriseops/enterpriseops-gym/
benchmark/enterpriseops/sample_ab/
benchmark/enterpriseops/results/
# Every live-run output dir is scratch (large trajectory dumps, re-derivable via
# live_ab.py). A single glob covers `live_results` + every `live_results_<suffix>/`
# variant (natural / rewind / restart / smoke / pilot / ab …) so a NEW arm's output
# dir cannot leak into `git add` the way live_results_restart_smoke/ did. The
# explicit per-dir lines below are now redundant but kept for readability/grep.
benchmark/enterpriseops/live_results*/
benchmark/enterpriseops/live_results/
benchmark/enterpriseops/live_results_natural/
# docs/172 rewind-arm live A/B output (large trajectory dumps + run logs — scratch,
# re-derivable via `live_ab.py --arms none block rewind`; the SCORED summary lives in
# docs/172, the re-runnable code is committed).
benchmark/enterpriseops/live_results_rewind_smoke/
benchmark/enterpriseops/live_results_rewind_smoke2/
benchmark/enterpriseops/live_results_rewind_pilot/
benchmark/enterpriseops/live_results_rewind_ab/
benchmark/enterpriseops/_rewind_*.log

# Transient harness state — the scheduled-agent lock is a per-machine runtime
# artifact, never source (the .claude/skills/ trees ARE tracked; this lock is not).
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock
# The maintainer's machine-local hooks (trajectory audit, posttool sensor, state
# cleanup) — personal rig, never shipped: a cold clone must not inherit hooks that
# need an installed `dos` or a $HOME script (they'd error on every tool call).
.claude/settings.local.json

# Research scratch — downloaded papers / scraped HTML (prior-art landscape work,
# e.g. the Arbiter-K paper dump). Not source; large and re-fetchable.
*.html
# …but the hand-authored interactive explainer visuals ARE source (stepped,
# zero-dependency walkthroughs of a real run — e.g. f2_visual.html, gate_visual.html,
# verify_visual.html, loop_visual.html). They live next to their data and the README
# links to them; keep them tracked. (f2_visual.html predates this and was force-added.)
!*_visual.html
benchmark/enterpriseops/live_results_natural_run/
benchmark/enterpriseops/live_results_natural_ab/
benchmark/enterpriseops/live_results_natural_smoke/
benchmark/enterpriseops/live_results_rewind_paired/
benchmark/enterpriseops/_ab_*.log
benchmark/enterpriseops/_natural_ab.log
benchmark/enterpriseops/_arms_seq.log
benchmark/enterpriseops/_run_arms_seq.sh

# The standardized runner's per-run stamp records (`python -m benchmark._run run …`
# writes benchmark/<bench>/_runs/run_<sha>_<entry>.json). Re-derivable scratch — the
# stamp records which kernel SHA a run was at (so `status` can flag stale numbers),
# but the SCORED summaries (RESULTS.md / RESULTS.txt) are the tracked artifact.
benchmark/*/_runs/

# One-off research scratch — the throwaway probe/verify/audit one-offs a session
# writes to interrogate the corpus, then discards. Re-derivable; the SCORED finding
# lives in the docs/NN_*.md or paper prose, never in these. Scoped to the dirs/
# extensions that are UNAMBIGUOUSLY scratch so a concurrent session's tracked work
# is never hidden from its own `git status` (the shared-tree discipline applied to
# .gitignore). Deliberately NOT a blanket `_probe_*`/`_verify_*` glob — those names
# are also used by in-flight feature work under benchmark/{enterpriseops,
# agentprocessbench}/, which stays visible. (Git has no inline-comment syntax —
# every annotation here is on its own line so the pattern lines stay literal.)
#
# a session-local audit (hardcoded ~/.claude path); never repo source:
/_audit_rl.py
*.err
# per-day re-run fact sheets (the paper PROSE is the tracked artifact):
paper/_VERIFIED_FACTS_*.md
paper/_rewrite_workflow.js
# (paper/figs_src/_audit_render.py is handled in paper/.gitignore — it sits under
# a `!figs_src/*.py` negation there, so it must be re-excluded in that file, not here.)

# Reverse-engineered Claude Code extraction artifacts (the docs/189 audit scratch:
# internal symbol names + line ranges decompiled from a third-party clone). Dropped
# from tracking 2026-06-08 ahead of the public seed; keep the family ignored so a
# regenerated dump never re-tracks. See PRE_PUBLISH_AUDIT_2026-06-08.md.
# NB a pattern line is ALL pattern — prose fused onto it (as happened here in the
# v0.22.0 seed: this pattern carried half a comment) silently matches nothing:
benchmark/_cc_*
# toolathlon facet probes (the SCORED result is in docs/157/177):
benchmark/toolathlon/_readback_independence.py
benchmark/toolathlon/_temporal_drill.py
benchmark/toolathlon/_temporal_facet.py
benchmark/toolathlon/_facet_beyond_state.py
benchmark/toolathlon/_w1_action_ack.py
benchmark/toolathlon/_probe_frontier_silent.py
# Throwaway tau2/consensus probes (docstring-labeled "Throwaway", unreferenced by
# any tracked code; hardcode a dev path). Listed explicitly per the no-blanket-glob
# rule above so a concurrent session's in-flight _probe_*/_verify_* stays visible.
# Added 2026-06-08 so the public-seed leak gate isn't tripped by scratch.
benchmark/agentprocessbench/_probe_map.py
benchmark/agentprocessbench/_probe_taskid.py
benchmark/agentprocessbench/writeadmit/_smoke_one.py
benchmark/enterpriseops/_verify_commons_collisions.py
# E3 head-to-head run logs (the SCORED result is in docs/206 §5):
benchmark/fleet_horizon/_e3_*.log
# enterpriseops live-run output logs (re-derivable via the harness):
benchmark/enterpriseops/_curable_schema_ab.log
benchmark/enterpriseops/_livelock_killshots.txt
benchmark/enterpriseops/_natural_ab_rewind.log
# writeadmit live outputs + smoke dirs (seed configs carry the Gemini key) — one glob
# covers live_results_writeadmit{,_sample,_m1_flash25,...}/, live_smoke*/, and *.log run logs.
benchmark/agentprocessbench/writeadmit/live_results*/
benchmark/agentprocessbench/writeadmit/live_smoke*/
benchmark/agentprocessbench/writeadmit/_run_*.log
# F2 STEP 3 (docs/245) live coordination run logs/results — verbose tau2 transcripts +
# the J summary; the FINDING lives in the doc, the raw run is regenerable + carries live
# API responses. (`_f2live.log`, `_f2results.txt`, `_smoke_out.txt`.)
benchmark/agentprocessbench/writeadmit/_f2*.txt
benchmark/agentprocessbench/writeadmit/_f2*.log
benchmark/agentprocessbench/writeadmit/_smoke_out.txt
# keep the bare patterns too (older runs wrote to cwd-relative dirs)
live_results_writeadmit/
live_results_writeadmit_sample/
# tau2coord (docs/233 port) live headless-claude arm — per-pair JSON cache carries live
# API responses; the J summary lives in benchmark/tau2coord/RESULTS.md, the cache is
# regenerable via `python -m benchmark.tau2coord.live_claude`.
live_results_tau2coord/
benchmark/tau2coord/live_results*/
# Agent-Diff live ΔB outputs (docs/237) — cached A/B rows carry live API responses + the
# run logs. One glob covers live_results{,_*}/ and the *.log run logs.
benchmark/agentdiff/live_results*/
benchmark/agentdiff/*.log
# RLVR Payoff-2 (docs/231) artifacts — regenerable corpus + SFT JSONL + run logs + job-ids.
# The corpus/JSONL derive from live tau2 runs (re-derivable via `rlvr_train generate`); the
# *.log carry run noise; the job-id/proxy/eval JSON are run state, not source.
rlvr_corpus*.jsonl
sft_poison*.jsonl
sft_clean*.jsonl
proxy_j2*.json
rlvr_j2*.json
rlvr_jobs*.json
_rlvr_*.log
benchmark/agentprocessbench/writeadmit/rlvr_corpus*.jsonl
benchmark/agentprocessbench/writeadmit/sft_*.jsonl
benchmark/agentprocessbench/writeadmit/live_results_cascade/

# Fleet-trajectory benchmark (docs/243) — regenerable label outputs mined from the
# live, NON-STATIONARY CC corpus. The code is committed; the labels are re-derivable
# (`python -m benchmark.fleet_trajectory.track_a --before <cutoff>`) and carry derived
# features only (paths/timestamps/verdicts — never raw narration, the §4.4 privacy split).
benchmark/fleet_trajectory/_track_*_labels.jsonl
benchmark/fleet_trajectory/_*.log
benchmark/agentprocessbench/writeadmit/live_results_fanout/

# Session scratch left at the repo ROOT — throwaway probe/data/audit one-offs a
# session wrote then discarded. Listed explicitly (per the no-blanket-glob rule
# above) so `git status` at the root is legible without hiding any concurrent
# session's tracked work. The SCORED finding always lives in a docs/NN_*.md or the
# paper prose, never in these. Added 2026-06-08.
#
# a poll helper with a hardcoded /c/work/dos path (never repo source):
/_poll_jobs.sh
# eval/probe JSON dumps + Box-folder-id scratch from a one-off data task:
/base_eval.json
/csv_files_data.json
/domain_file_counts.json
/domain_folder_ids.json
/economic_domains_folder_id.txt
# a dated pre-publish sensitivity audit (local working note; its findings are
# actioned in-tree — the .gitignore family above cites it as rationale):
/PRE_PUBLISH_AUDIT_*.md
# Stop-hook output: the maintainer's machine-local trajectory-audit hook (see
# settings.local.json note above) writes its report to the repo root on session
# end; a session's own audit must never ride into the public seed as an
# untracked file (2026-06-10 audit):
/trajectory-audit-*.md
# the paper's per-day critical-claims re-derivation note — the SSOT sibling of the
# already-ignored paper/_VERIFIED_FACTS_*.md (the paper PROSE is the tracked artifact):
paper/_AUDIT_*.md

