# Live-run output dirs written to the repo ROOT (the fleet-scale F1/F2/F3 harnesses —
# docs/245/253/255 — wrote cascade/coord/fanout JSON to cwd=root instead of under
# benchmark/). Large, re-derivable trajectory dumps that carry live API responses;
# the SCORED J figure lives in the doc, the runnable code is committed. The
# ROOT-ANCHORED glob (leading `/`) is the structural fix: it stops a NEW root-level
# `live_results_<suffix>/` from leaking into `git add` the way these three did,
# WITHOUT shadowing the legitimate tracked dirs deeper in the tree. Added 2026-06-08.
/live_results*/

# Dated cross-vendor binding proof output (the docs/217 vendor-agnostic-kernel proof
# run — baseline/pip-install/hook-dialect/MCP-wiring transcripts + config snapshots &
# .bak backups). A timestamped scratch dir; re-derivable by re-running the proof. The
# root-anchored `_*_proof_*/` glob also catches a future re-run's fresh timestamp.
# Added 2026-06-08.
/_vendor_proof_*/
/*_proof_2026-*/
# Isolated Go build caches a session points $GOCACHE at to dodge the shared-cache
# lock contention from a concurrent fleet (the docs memory's `go test` wedge). All
# are transient, re-derivable scratch — never commit one. The `/go/.cache_bench`
# was the first; the glob catches `.cache_goal`, `.cache_goal_audit`, and any future
# session's private cache dir.
/go/.cache_bench
/go/.cache_*/
# A session may also point $GOCACHE at a root-level dir (e.g. `.gocache-stats-verify/`
# while rebuilding the bundled plugin binaries) — catch those too.
/.gocache-*/

# Live host-hook PROBE scratch (manual cross-vendor integration debugging). These
# wire a real agent's hook to this machine's paths and DELIBERATELY feed a
# self-modifying write to prove the SELF_MODIFY deny fires — so they must NEVER be
# committed (a checked-out probe that targets the real kernel propagates the
# fail-open hazard, and is what truncated arbiter.py to 'x'). The SAFE, committed
# equivalent is scripts/selfmodify_hook_probe.py (sacrificial workspace). The
# /.gemini/ runtime config is per-machine (absolute paths + the live MCP wiring),
# like a local settings file — not a portable example. The globs catch the whole
# probe family a session spins up: _gemini_hook*, _prove_gemini*, _run_proof*,
# _dos_hook*, and the _VERDICT.txt they write.
/_gemini_hook*
/_prove_gemini*
/_run_proof*
/_dos_hook*
/_*VERDICT*.txt
/.gemini/

# Scoreboard sweep/seed staging — the corpus run's clones, the per-repo
# (identity-carrying, operator-only) verdict JSONs, and the FOREIGN named pages
# a seed run stages for review. Publishing to gh-pages is an owner action (#98);
# a run's output never gets tracked. The TRACKED scoreboard artifacts are only
# under docs/scoreboard/ (the index root, methodology, report, page #1).
/scoreboard-out/
/scoreboard-seed-out/
# any suffixed staging dir a run uses (scoreboard-out-pilot/, -seed-out2/, …):
/scoreboard-out*/
/scoreboard-seed-out*/
/scoreboard-seed-out*.log
/scoreboard-out*.log
/scoreboard-seed-out*.manifest.json
